replies.body:
We all have moments where we aren't at our best, and nobody is faulting you for that. We all know what it feels like to have that rage building and it's not that we're trying to punish you for that, we're merely trying to keep a safe environment where people don't walk away feeling upset/depressed. Feeling upset about being slighted is normal for everyone. It's how you handle that rage that makes all the difference. 

I do commend you for taking time to reflect and even *moreso* for stepping forward and apologizing even when it's not needed. I'm here to serve you guys, and I look out for everyone and try to bring out the best in everyone when I can.

{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}
